
<div class="wrap profile">

  <div id='assumerole'>
      <h2>Select Your AWS Profile</h2>
      <div class="form">
        <div class="row">
        <% profiles.each do |profile|%>
          <div class="box col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3 col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-4">
            <input type="submit" name="profile" class="button" value="<%= profile %>" />
          </div>
        <% end %>
        <!-- <input type="button" name="profile" class="reset button" value="reset"/> -->
        <div class="box col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3 col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-4">
          <input type="input" name="profile_mfa" class="mfa" placeholder="mfa token" />
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <a class=" col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3 col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-4 help" href="#ex1" rel="modal:open">help</a>
  </div>

 <div id="ex1" style="display:none;">
   <h2>What is Docker AWS Proxy?</h2>
   <p>The docker AWS proxy service allows us to simulate what conditions will exist in a container running on an EC2 instance within AWS. We can assume roles for our containers, giving them the ability to query the ec2 metadata service locally on your own machine!</p>
   <p>Docker AWS Proxy supports multiple profiles which are discovered from <code>~/.aws/credentials</code>.  Select the profile here and it will be used to authorize future requets
   listing and assuming the roles and discovering your MFA token's serial.</p>
   <h2>MFA Token Option</h2>
   <p>
     If you enter MFA below, a session token for this profile can be used
     in lieu of an MFA token for role assumption later.  This token can be good for
     as much as one day (86400 seconds).
   </p>
  <br><a href="#" rel="modal:close">Close</a> or press ESC</p>
 </div>


 <div id="logging_in">
   <div class="loading"></div>

 </div>
</div>
